profile:
Ridge Meadows Roofing was founded in September 2001 by Trevor McDonald, who has more than 25 years of roofing experience. We specialize in residential asphalt shingle re-roofing and are certified CertainTeed ShingleMasters. Trevor is the son of Brian and Dorothy McDonald, who  successfully owned and operated McDonald’s Flooring in Maple Ridge for over 40 years. After taking several business and marketing classes in college, and then learning the trade over six years, Trevor decided to operate his own roofing company. Beginning as a modest residential re-roofing and repairing business, Ridge Meadows Roofing has grown into a full-fledged team of skilled professionals, who consistently provide great service and demonstrate their workmanship on each and every roof. But even with a talented team of roofing professionals, Trevor carefully oversees all tasks.
 
We service the following areas and beyond; Maple Ridge, Pitt Meadows, Port Coquitlam, Coquitlam, Port Moody, Langley, Surrey, Burnaby and Vancouver.

Bathroom renovations don't have to be confusing or complicated.  At Coast Bathing we are here to make the process simple and fast!  We are bathroom specialists!  Whether you are wanting to refresh your outdated bathroom, expand or reconfigure your space or make updates to be suitable for aging-in-place, we have the team to do it all!

We have researched and found beautiful, cost and time effective products that will refresh your old bathroom in less than a week, and give you years of maintenance free living.

We also offer "senior" specific solutions. As we grow older, even little things like taking a bath, which should be a pleasure, can quite literally become a real pain. But putting up with this doesn’t have to be your future!  From tub cut-outs, to tub to shower conversions or walk-in tubs-  There is a simple and effective solution, a Bathing Solution by COAST!
 
We offer competitive rates, custom solutions, and personalized service.

Blue Ocean Construction is an award-winning Residential and Commercial General Contracting Firm serving clients in the Vancouver and Lower Mainland areas.  Now in our 32nd year, at Blue Ocean Construction we’ll take the time to fully understand your requirements and provide you with the information to need to make an informed decision on your construction needs. As an accredited member of the Better Business Bureau for 20+ years, we’ve achieved an A+ rating.  We are a member of the Canadian Home Builder’s Association, and of Renomark.  Winner of multiple awards and accreditation's, we’re proud of our team, and our continuous commitment to excellence.
For further information and to view our photo gallery visit our website http://blueoceanconstruction.com/

profile:
City & Country Contracting aims to be the industry leader in renovations and construction management. Our promise to our clients is to make every effort to take any unnecessary headaches and stress out of a renovation project by ensuring delivery of a quality project on time, and on budget. We work with a number of local contracting and supply companies to ensure we support the local economy within the communities we serve.
.
We believe in Sustainable Construction practices where we aim to eliminate (negative) health and environmental impacts in the construction process. At City & Country Contracting, we work to minimize construction waste and maximize the reuse of materials to lessen the impact of projects on the environment while promoting innovative solar and geothermal energy solutions. Renewable and sustainable energy programs are the key to our children’s future and City & Country Contracting promises to build projects using the greenest methods and materials available!
.
Company Founder- Shayne Finskars
Shayne started general construction by taking on residential renovations in his first home and using his lengthy carpentry and construction experience to conduct the renovations. During this time he gained recognition from family, friends and others over social media for the custom look and quality of these renovations. Many neighbours, friends and acquaintances asked him to take on the general contractor role for their renovations, provide advice or take on the project completely. He gained significant experience and furthered his education in the renovation and building science fields. As a result, he has taken on a number of general contractor projects while supplementing his knowledge through general residential construction course work and supply management research. As a result Shayne has gained a great appreciation for the general contracting process, attained significant knowledge on a variety of construction materials, and developed significant relationships with clientele. The progression/development in modern building sciences, and being able to build beautiful projects have motivated him to do outstanding work. profile:
Usar is a custom, design-build, contracting company that organizes and builds every part of your dream home. We are a full-service building solution company specializing in high-end residential construction to create uniquely personalized living spaces.  | Office: 778-987-6196 | E-mail: info@usar.ca | www.usar.ca
-- --
Usar is a custom home consulting and contracting company founded in 2004. We service the Greater Vancouver Area by offering a full-service custom home building solution, from concept to finished project.

Our vision is that by working with all aspects of the home building process, including architectural, construction and design professionals from the beginning, we can create a more seamless home construction experience and superior final product. We believe that wonderful homes get made when design and unique ideas meet solid technical and structural components.

Members of the Usar management team have worked in all aspects of the home building process, including construction site work, home building material sales, spec home building and beyond. After having the opportunity to explore the many different avenues of general contracting, we’ve established that custom homes are our specialty because of our comprehensive skill set and experience in the industry.

To us, your home is a crucial component of your life. It's where you spend a large part of your day, and being able to have a role in choosing and designing the comforts you look for in a home is a way to enhance that daily experience. 
-- --
Usar’s Five Phase Building Approach

PROJECT CONSULTATION
We will meet with you to find out exactly how we can help you build the home of your dreams. Using our more than 20 years of industry experience and your vision, we will work together to create a house that you and your family can make into a home.

BUILDING PREPARATION
We draft up the building plan to apply for the appropriate permits and permissions to build your home. Our experience in multiple different cities and municipalities has given us an advantage in pre-building preparation. Let us handle the paperwork so you can focus on the aspects of your new home that matter to you most.

INTERIOR DESIGN
Our friends at Inter-mind Design have won multiple Georgie and Ovation awards for their interior design excellence throughout British Columbia. Our partnership with them helps us provide you with experienced and knowledgeable design professionals who will make your new house a stylish, functional and unforgettable home. By having a specific interior design focus before building, we can ensure that the home will be created as the perfect canvas for your furnishing plans.

BUILDING PHASE
A structured process before building results in faster building times, more structurally sound houses, and reduced waste on production sites. We want you to love your custom home, which is why we have regular check-ins with clients during the building phase to ensure that project aspects are coming to life exactly as planned. Our experienced and talented staff allow us to offer luxury building services in Metro Vancouver and BC’s surrounding areas.

POST PROJECT CHECK-IN
We want to make sure that you are happy with the results once your custom home is completed. We meet with all of our customers after the building phase is finished to ensure that everything is in order and to see if there is anything else we can do to complete your dream home.

--  --
Mission
Usar is a custom design-build contracting company that will custom design and build every part of your project. Usar will build a house that will become your home. Usar is growing into all different contracting levels and makes the finest custom homes and affordable homes for all communities. 

Vision
Contracting is not limited to the building’s technical parts; it must respect good design and ideas. We are dedicated to working along with designers to create function, coziness and life value in every dwelling. We value and appreciate the workmanship of every trade and work together.


Usar Contracting & Design Inc.

profile:
Building your dreams with blackbelt precision, that's our motto at Black Belt. We keep a tight crew at Black Belt to maintain our reputation as skilled, high end builders with an eye for detail. We commit the same level of quality from the smallest project to a complete home renovation, and we've maintained that from the beginning. With our uniquely qualified crew we can tackle any project thrown our way, from interior tiles to high end hardwood decks. With the highest standards for cleanliness and quality you will not be disappointed with your finished Black Belt project, give us a call today for a free quote! For more photos of our latest projects check out our instagram @blackbeltcontracting_inc

Meet our Team!

Fraser (Director of Operations) 
Clients are always excited to see Fraser’s evident knowledge and passion – a result of his range of experience, commitment, and drive. Born and raised in the lower mainland, Fraser has been in construction for almost two decades. Believing in a lead-by-example approach, Fraser thoroughly enjoys being on site with the crew – to offer this experience and pass it on. He is involved in every step of the process to turn your dreams into a reality, which keeps him busy! In his time out of work, Fraser enjoys keeping fit, with a history in martial arts, and is helped along by running after his small collection of dogs and cats. 

Katie (Director of Design)
Black Belt’s darling – Katie – joined the Black Belt team over a decade ago and her precision, attention to detail and energy all combined to lead to the fruition of Katie’s main joy: her tiling. From intricate designs, to pristine execution, clients are astounded with what Katie delivers. After pouring her love into her work, Katie manages to find some more for her sporting life, where she also coaches. She credits her work ethic to her father, grandfather and other family members, whom she enjoys spending her free time with.

profile:
exceptional design.
extraordinary innovation.

It all begins with an idea. 
Maybe you want to launch a business. 
Or maybe you are just tired of what you have and want a change. 

Modera Developments has over a 13 years of experience in many facets of home renovations, design, construction, and project management. 
With our on-staff team of trade specialists, we’re able to offer competitive rates and a one-stop shop for your next build. 

Floor to Ceiling.
Renovations are a big undertaking, even the smallest of projects. 
We can help make these simple and easy with painting, flooring, ceiling resurfacing, and advice on best practices. 

Everything in-Between.
You may have the floors and ceilings covered, but what about the walls? We offer in-house trade specialists for plumbing, electrical, and insulation (spray foam or fiberglass). 
We also offer drywall services.

Providing the Right Support.
As part of being a one-stop shop, we can repair or replace your existing roof, from just the tiles/singles to a full replacement. 
Framing services are also available.

From the Ground up.
Starting from scratch? Looking to build a new lane home or coach house on your property? 
Let Modera design and build your home extension. 
We’re always on the cutting edge of trends for modular and condensed-footing homes, and can recommend options to maximize livability and budget.

profile:
WHO WE ARE
KØBEN Construction is a City of Vancouver licensed, fully insured, and owner-operated general contracting company. We specialize in small to medium-sized residential home improvement projects, including renovations for houses and condominiums in the Greater Vancouver Area.

WHAT WE DO
We focus on home improvement projects for the typical Vancouver homeowner, just like us. Maybe you need to modernize and open up an existing room or floor of your house. Or you have a vision for a functional and design-conscious kitchen that brings everyone together. Or, perhaps you’re looking to expand your living space by upgrading your front or back yard for outdoor entertaining.  For any size project, we can help!

WHY WORK WITH US?
We understand the physical and emotional toll a renovation can take and we therefore put our heart and soul into every project to make the experience as personal and stress free as possible. Cleanliness and respect are always central when it comes to interacting with clients, neighbors and building staff. The highest degree of professional standards at every level of the organization have made word-of-mouth recommendations and repeat clients the biggest source of our business.

profile:
At Woodcraft, we love what we do! Building, repairing & maintaining homes, or multi-family strata corporations can be challenging at times, but that is when it gets fun.

Having challenges & solving problems is what makes the construction industry so rewarding. Having something new & exciting to tackle each day is what we at Woodcraft love to do. We know that there are lots of challenges & decisions to be made, but that is what we are here for. A problem is only a problem if you allow it to be.

We approach every project with enthusiasm and a wealth of knowledge and expertise. Good communication with our clients makes every project unique and personal, and we endeavor to make all our customers projects, big or small, an easy and enjoyable experience. Woodcraft understands the importance of using the right tools, the best trades and supplies for the job, with a serious attention to detail.

The company was formed by Rudi Nosper, who is a Red Seal Journeyman Carpenter. Rudi saw the need in the industry for quality workmanship and project management, which he is dedicated to bringing to his customers. Rudi started in the construction industry at 11 years of age working with his dad as a painter. Though painting was not his forte, Rudi saw that construction was in his blood. Now, after years in the industry, Rudi, along with his wife, Candace, who handles Office Administration, and his brother David, a Journeyman Carpenter as well, they have been providing renovations since 2003. 

Throughout our years of experience handling renovations and additions of all types, we saw a need for strata property maintenance, which has grown to 50% of our business. Our goal is to be the last renovation, repair, or update required for decades to come.

Use Woodcraft’s expertise as they guide you through each step of the process and help you choose from the many design options out there so you can truly say:

YOU “LOVE WHERE YOU LIVE!”

Norquest Homes has been in the residential construction industry for over twenty years specializing in new home construction, renovations, and construction management.


We take care of it all - from design, plan submission, inspections and final occupancy. As a hands on construction company, we spend more time directly on your job than the larger companies. This allows us to keep you up to date on the progress of your project and flexible in making changes when needed. Most importantly, being on site allows us to deliver the highest quality of workmanship so that you end up with the best finished product.

Looking for a custom built home, a finished basement, or an addition to your space? Let Norquest Homes do all the work so that all you have to do is relax and enjoy your new place.
